gomodel:SYNGO_722  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 1i IL1RAPL1 coimmunoprecipitates with PSD-95\nFig. 2c Il1RAPL1 colocalizes with PSD-95\n\nLiteral: \"Finally, the interaction between IL1RAPL1 and PSD-95 was biochemically proven by pull-down and immunoprecipitation experiments in transfected COS-7 cells and in vivo from neuronal protein extract.\" \"The endogenous IL1RAPL1 mostly colocalized with PSD-95 and Shank proteins (percent of IL1RAPL1 colocalization with PSD-95\"\n\n7/6/2017 Pim\n- PSD-95 is a marker protein for glutamatergic synapses.\n- IL1RAPL1 has a TM domain.. Experimental description: Coimmunoprecipitatiopn experiments are made in rat brain extract.\nColocalization with endogenous PDD-95 is made in rat hippocampal neurons.\n\nLiteral form M&M\n\"Low-density hippocampal neuronal cultures were prepared from E18-E19 rat hippocampi as previously described\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_722" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

